article.description: Ethan Telfair scored 30 points -- including the buzzer-beating game-winning jumper -- and Idaho State dealt Weber State its first Big Sky Conference loss, 69-68 on Saturday.
article.headline: Telfair beats buzzer, Idaho State beats Weber State 69-68
article.linkText: Telfair beats buzzer, Idaho State beats Weber State 69-68
article.story: POCATELLO, Idaho -- Ethan Telfair scored 30 points -- including the buzzer-beating game-winning jumper -- and Idaho State dealt Weber State its first Big Sky Conference loss, 69-68 on Saturday. Weber State's Joel Bolomboy hit a jumper with 31 seconds left to take a one-point lead. Moments later after a turnover, Telfair walked the ball up, then dribbled to the right wing, crossed-over a defender, and watched his jumper from just inside the 3-point line fall as he slid on his rear out of bounds. Telfair scored the last 11 points of the game for Idaho State (8-10, 3-3 Big Sky), including seven consecutive free throws. He hit four 3-pointers and had six assists. Geno Luzcando added 15 points. Weber State (13-6, 5-1) led by six with 2:35 left. The Wildcats were paced by Jeremy Senglin with 20 points. Bolomboy finished with 13 points and seven boards, and Dusty Baker added 11 points.
